# Reading List: AI + Customer Success

> Curated resources for CS leaders building AI-first operations.

## Essential Reads

- **[The AI-First Customer Success Playbook](https://www.gainsight.com/guides/)** — Gainsight's evolving framework for AI in CS operations
- **[Anthropic's Claude Documentation](https://docs.anthropic.com/)** — Understanding LLM capabilities and limitations for business applications
- **[The Effortless Experience](https://www.gartner.com/en/sales/insights/effortless-experience)** — CEB/Gartner research on customer effort reduction (foundational CS thinking)
- **[Scaling Customer Success](https://www.strikedeck.com/)** — Frameworks for scaled and tech-touch engagement models

## On AI Strategy

- **[AI for Business Leaders](https://www.deeplearning.ai/)** — Andrew Ng's courses on practical AI deployment
- **[The AI-First Company](https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/the-ai-first-company/9781098104207/)** — Ash Fontana on building organisations around AI capabilities
- **[Prompt Engineering Guide](https://www.promptingguide.ai/)** — Practical techniques for getting better outputs from LLMs

## On CS Operations & Strategy

- **[Customer Success: How Innovative Companies Are Reducing Churn](https://www.amazon.co.uk/Customer-Success-Innovative-Companies-Reducing/dp/1119167965)** — Nick Mehta, Dan Steinman — The CS bible
- **[The Outcome Generation](https://www.theoutcomegeneration.com/)** — Paul Henderson on outcomes-based CS
- **[Farm Don't Hunt](https://www.amazon.co.uk/Farm-Dont-Hunt-Definitive-Customer/dp/0692620931)** — Guy Nirpaz on the economics of customer success

## Newsletters & Communities

- **[The CS Café](https://www.thecscafe.com/)** — Hakan Ozturk's weekly CS newsletter
- **[Gain Grow Retain](https://www.gaingrowretain.com/)** — CS community and podcast
- **[Lenny's Newsletter](https://www.lennysnewsletter.com/)** — Product and growth insights (relevant for product-led CS)

---

*This list is a living document. Contributions and suggestions welcome.*
